car%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe'd%20also%20given%20birth%20to%20our%20son%20in%202020%2C%20and%20I%20was%20pregnant%20with%20our%20daughter.%20Our%20priorities%20had%20changed%20since%20we%20initially%20dreamt%20about%20our%20wedding.%20I%20questioned%20whether%20the%20money%20would%20be%20better%20spent%20on%20buying%20what%20they%20needed%20and%20spoiling%20them%20without%20worrying%20about%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202021%2C%20when%20COVID%20still%20threatened%20to%20disrupt%20our%20wedding%20plans%2C%20my%20husband%20asked%20if%20we%20should%20elope%20instead.%20We%20had%20been%20discussing%20the%20wedding%20less%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20we'd%20recently%20had%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felopement-regrets-mistakes-to-avoid-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efriend%20elope%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20loved%20the%20experience.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20I%20thought%20about%20elopement%2C%20the%20more%20I%20liked%20the%20sound%20of%20it.%20It%20would%20be%20much%20less%20stressful%20and%20easier%20to%20plan%2C%20and%20we%20would%20save%20a%20small%20fortune.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuckily%2C%20we%20hadn't%20booked%20anything%20yet%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20to%20abandon%20our%20wedding%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e5a6063d-5b1c-4998-bee2-48a231b0b81b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWithin%20a%20few%20months%20of%20planting%20the%20idea%2C%20we%20eloped%20at%20a%20registrar's%20office%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20elopement%20was%20four%20years%20earlier%20than%20expected%20because%20we%20wouldn't%20have%20to%20save%20the%20large%20sum%20needed%20for%20a%20big%20wedding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20morning%2C%20my%20friend%2C%20who%20would%20be%20one%20of%20our%20witnesses%2C%20came%20to%20my%20house%20to%20help%20me%20get%20ready.%20My%20grandparents%20came%20over%2C%20too%2C%20helping%20to%20get%20the%20kids%20ready.%20Connor%20went%20to%20the%20venue%20on%20the%20train%2C%20and%20I%20drove%20with%20the%20kids.%20My%20grandparents%20would%20have%20the%20kids%20while%20we%20were%20married%20and%20meet%20us%20afterward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20no%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhated-going-to-friends-weddings-now-miss-them-older-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewedding-day%20jitters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20no%20nerves%20at%20all.%20I%20wasn't%20worried%20about%20the%20schedule%2C%20drunken%20drama%20between%20guests%2C%20or%20looking%20a%20certain%20way%20for%20a%20photographer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20read%20our%20vows%20to%20each%20other%2C%20making%20promises%20with%20only%20two%20friends%20present.%20I%20misspoke%20during%20the%20vows%20and%20didn't%20feel%20embarrassed.%20Finally%2C%20we%20signed%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcost-of-marriage-license-by-state-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emarriage%20license%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20sealed%20the%20day%20with%20a%20kiss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfterward%2C%20my%20kids%20and%20grandparents%20met%20us%20for%20informal%20photos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20relaxed%20day%20without%20pressure%2C%20hassle%2C%20or%20expectations.%20We%20only%20paid%20a%20few%20hundred%20dollars%20for%20the%20whole%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20expected%2C%20the%20money%20we%20would%20have%20spent%20on%20the%20wedding%20ended%20up%20going%20on%20the%20kids.%20We%20could%20get%20things%20like%20outdoor%20play%20equipment%20and%20not%20think%20twice%20about%20paying%20for%20it%2C%20as%20the%20money%20had%20already%20been%20saved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20could%20do%20it%20over%20again%2C%20I%20would%20have%20paid%20extra%20to%20allow%20guests%20to%20attend%20the%20ceremony%20at%20the%20registry%20office%2C%20because%20it%20would%20have%20meant%20a%20lot%20to%20have%20my%20parents%20and%20grandparents%20present%20to%20celebrate%20with%20us.%20It%20would%20still%20have%20been%20chill%20and%20cheap%2C%20but%20it%20would%20have%20involved%20the%20people%20we%20love%