20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20about%20what%20we're%20building%20as%20kind%20of%20the%20Canva%20for%20video%2C%26quot%3B%20Kossnick%2C%20Hypernatural's%20CEO%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-canva%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECanva%3C%2Fa%3E%20proved%20that%20you%20don't%20need%20a%20degree%20for%20graphic%20design%20to%20be%20your%20passion%2C%20Hypernatural%20wants%20to%20prove%20that%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20know%20Adobe%20After%20Effects%20to%20turn%20ideas%20into%20videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFounded%20in%202023%20by%20Kossnick%20and%20Taylor%20Hughes%20(CTO)%2C%20who%20first%20met%20while%20working%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFacebook%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Hypernatural's%20video%20generation%20tech%20uses%20an%20average%20of%2015%20different%20AI%20models%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-deepmind%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E's%20Veo%203%2C%20Lightricks'%20LTX%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-startup-unicorns-with-tiny-teams-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBlack%20Forest%20Labs%3C%2Fa%3E'%20Flux.%20Kossnick%20said%20that%20the%20platform's%20speed%20is%20a%20key%20selling%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20building%20a%20foundation%20model%2C%20we're%20building%20the%20technology%20to%20understand%20and%20deploy%20the%20foundation%20models%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20Kossnick%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20startup%20told%20Business%20Insider%20exclusively%20that%20it%20has%20raised%20a%20total%20of%20%249.2%20million%20in%20funding%20across%20two%20rounds%20from%20investors%20AIX%20Ventures%2C%20Underscore%20VC%2C%20Adverb%20Ventures%2C%20Character%20Capital%2C%20and%2043%20VC.%20Part%20of%20Hypernatural's%20total%20funding%20includes%20a%20%246.8%20million%20seed%20round%20led%20by%20AIX%20that%20closed%20in%20December%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrently%20a%20team%20of%20five%2C%20Hypernatural's%20funding%20will%20go%20toward%20hiring%20(Kossnick%20emphasized%20its%20focus%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-talent-wars-startups-compete-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erecruiting%20engineering%20%3C%2Fa%3Etalent)%20and%20building%20out%20the%20platform's%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20throwing%20money%20on%20what's%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20Kossnick%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20video%20generation%20startups%20have%20been%20raising%20capital%20left%20and%20right.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoonvalley-raises-84-million-ai-hollywood-tool-studios-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMoonvalley%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20its%20own%20AI%20video%20model%2C%20told%20BI%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20it%20raised%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2484%20million.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-generative-video-image-hedra-startup-raise-a16z-pitch-deck-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHedra%2C%20another%20AI%20video%20creation%3C%2Fa%3E%20platform%2C%20announced%20a%20%2432%20million%20Series%20A%20round%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225bcbccdd-3db9-45ae-b27d-249065624b13%5C%22%3EBuilding%20for%20both%20creators%20and%20everyday%20consumers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20excited%20to%20try%20and%20buy%20products%20that%20support%20their%20creativity%2C%26quot%3B%20Kossnick%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20sort%20of%20where%20we%20see%20consumer%20and%20the%20'prosumer'%20creator%20economy%20merge.%20Sometimes%20you're%20creating%20for%20other%20people%20%E2%80%A6%20sometimes%20you're%20creating%20for%20you%20because%20you%20wanted%20to%20see%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20story.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20quite%20easy%20to%20navigate%20Hypernatural's%20tools.%20For%20instance%2C%20I%20made%20a%2054-second%20video%20(with%2020%20AI-generated%20images%20Hypernatural%20created)%20about%20a%20journalist%20writing%20a%20story%20in%20roughly%20a%20minute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20the%20platform%20works%3A%20Users%20input%20a%20text%20prompt%20and%20choose%20a%20style%20(such%20as%20anime)%2C%20length%2C%20and%20size%20of%20the%20video.%20It%20then%20generates%20a%20full%20script%20(users%20can%20also%20use%20an%20existing%20script%2C%20and%20paid%20subscribers%20can%20upload%20audio%20files).%20At%20this%20stage%2C%20users%20can%20choose%20from%20a%20selection%20of%20narrator%20voices%20and%20characters%20(custom-made%20characters%20require%20a%20paid%20subscription).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHypernatural's%20platform%20then%20spits%20out%20a%20video%20and%20brings%20the%20user%20to%20an%20editing%20page%20where%20they%20can%20rearrange%20scenes%2C%20edit%20the%20script%2C%20and%20either%20reanimate%20scenes%20or%20pull%20from%20its%20stock%20library%20of%20AI-generated%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20users%20really%20care%20about%20the%20rights%20of%20all%20of%20the%20images%20and%20videos%20that%20we%20create%2C%26quot%3B%20Kossnick%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20only%20working%20with%20models%20that%20are%20providing%20us%20with%20commercial%20rights%2C%20which%20would%20pass%20on%20to%20users%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20%26quot%3Bcreator%26quot%3B%20tier%20annual%20subscription%20costs%20%2412%20a%20month%2C%20and%20higher%20tiers%20that%20offer%20more%20content%20credits%20and%20custom%20characters%20go%20up%20to%20%2448%20a%20month.%20It%20also%20has%20a%20free%20tier%20with%20limited%20access%20to%20the%20platform's%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHypernatural%20said%20it%20has%20more%20than%201%20million%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Kossnick%20said%20Hypernatural's%20early%20users%20include%20%26quot%3Bniche%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcreator-e