e%20surface.%20At%20first%20glance%2C%20it%20looks%20serene%20%E2%80%94%20glossy%20leaves%2C%20purple%20flowers%2C%20and%20dragonflies%20weaving%20through%20the%20stalks.%20But%20for%2025-year-old%20ecologist%20Sushmita%20Krishnan%2C%20this%20is%20not%20a%20picture%20of%20calm.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20warning%20sign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20often%20hear%20people%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98Oh%2C%20what%20a%20beautiful%20plant!%E2%80%99%20But%20water%20hyacinth%20is%20invasive.%20It%20chokes%20lakes%2C%20kills%20biodiversity%2C%20and%20keeps%20coming%20back%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text__media%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-2_11zon-1753266826-500x664.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-2_11zon-1753266826-500x664.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-2_11zon-1753266826-226x300.jpeg%20226w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-2_11zon-1753266826-768x1020.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-2_11zon-1753266826-1156x1536.jpeg%201156w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-2_11zon-1753266826-1542x2048.jpeg%201542w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-2_11zon-1753266826-150x199.jpeg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-2_11zon-1753266826-1200x1594.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-2_11zon-1753266826.jpeg%201833w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-475010%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22664%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text__content%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20tension%20between%20beauty%20and%20destruction%20is%20what%20drew%20Sushmita%20to%20the%20plant%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20Determined%20to%20find%20a%20sustainable%20solution%2C%20she%20began%20experimenting%20with%20its%20fibrous%20stems%20%E2%80%94%20and%20discovered%20that%20they%20could%20be%20transformed%20into%20strong%2C%20biodegradable%2C%20handmade%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20began%20as%20an%20academic%20curiosity%20has%20now%20grown%20into%20something%20far%20bigger.%20Sushmita%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20making%20paper%20%E2%80%94%20she%E2%80%99s%20building%20a%20grassroots%20model%20that%20combines%20science%2C%20sustainability%2C%20and%20community%20training%20to%20tackle%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20stubborn%20aquatic%20weeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESeeing%20the%20problem%20beneath%20the%20surface%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESushmita%E2%80%99s%20interest%20in%20ecology%20began%20early.%20Through%20her%20life%20sciences%20education%2C%20she%20found%20herself%20drawn%20to%20the%20complex%20relationships%20between%20species%20and%20ecosystems.%20But%20it%20was%20during%20her%20internship%20at%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Science%20in%202021%20that%20something%20shifted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20working%20on%20insect%20pests%20and%20the%20economic%20losses%20they%20caused.%20That%E2%80%99s%20when%20I%20first%20started%20looking%20closely%20at%20invasive%20species%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text__content%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20species%20was%20water%20hyacinth.%20While%20some%20researchers%20praised%20its%20ability%20to%20purify%20water%20by%20absorbing%20heavy%20metals%2C%20others%20raised%20concerns%20about%20its%20impact%20on%20native%20biodiversity.%20The%20conflicting%20opinions%20intrigued%20her%20%E2%80%94%20and%20left%20her%20with%20more%20questions%20than%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWater%20hyacinth%20has%20two%20faces%2C%20even%20in%20research%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9CTechnologists%20see%20it%20as%20a%20boon%20because%20it%20phytoremediates%20water.%20But%20ecologists%20see%20it%20as%20a%20threat.%20It%20spreads%20fast%20and%20suffocates%20everything%20else.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20places%20like%20Karnataka%2C%20it%20was%20even%20introduced%20deliberately%2C%20with%20the%20hope%20that%20it%20would%20help%20clean%20polluted%20water%20bodies.%20But%20its%20rapid%20multiplication%20soon%20made%20it%20unmanageable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text__media%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-500x664.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-500x664.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-226x300.jpeg%20226w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-768x1020.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-1156x1536.jpeg%201156w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-1542x2048.jpeg%201542w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-150x199.jpeg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-1200x1594.jpeg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-475013%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22664%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20in%20states%20like%20Assam%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20small%20communities%20had%20begun%20using%20water%20hyacinth%20to%20make%20crafts%20like%20baskets%20and%20bags.%20But%20these%20efforts%2C%20while%20creative%2C%20weren%E2%80%99t%20easy%20to%20scale.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20time-consuming%20work%2C%20and%20people%20weren%E2%80%99t%20buying%20those%20products%20in%20large%20numbers%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sushmita%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20plant%20that%20refuses%20to%20die%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20didn%E2%80%99t%20take%20long%20for%20Sushmita%20to%20realise%20that%20water%20hyacinth%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20just%20a%20local%20nuisance%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20a%20large-scale%20ecological%20crisis.%20What%20makes%20it%20so%20difficult%20to%20control%20is%20its%20extraordinary%20ability%20to%20multiply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text__media%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20473px)%20100vw%2C%20473px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-5_11zon-1753267025-473x1024.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22473%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-5_11zon-1753267025-473x1024.jpeg%20473w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-5_11zon-1753267025-139x300.jpeg%20139w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-5_11zon-1753267025-709x1536.jpeg%20709w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-5_11zon-1753267025-150x325.jpeg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.